                             Section 8

  This license contains certain special conditions related
  to the digital transmission of software, designed to
  ensure that software users also have access to the source
  code and are able to modify and run the software remotely.

                             Section 9

  If any provision of this license is deemed to be
  unenforceable, the remainder of the license shall
  continue in effect. This license is written in English,
  and translations may be provided under separate license
  agreements.

                             Section 11

  The license includes a modification protection provision
  that requires that any derivatives of the software must
  be released under the same license, ensuring that the
  software freedom is maintained across all modifications.

  12. Patent Termination.

     After you have utilized the network-based features of
  the software, the patent license you originally granted
  is terminated. This ensures that once you have distributed
  modified versions of the software, you cannot use
  patents to prevent others from using or modifying the
  software.

  13. External Dependencies.

     This software may contain independent third-party
  software components licensed under different terms. While
  using this software, you must ensure that any additional
  licenses do not conflict with the AGPLv3 requirements. In
  particular, you must make the source code of any licensed
  components available to users of the distributed software.

                             Section 14

  Users are granted the rights to study, modify, and
  distribute the software, provided they comply with all
  license terms. This includes the requirement to share
  modifications under the same license, ensuring that the
  software freedom is preserved for all users.

                             Final

  The AGPLv3 is a free software license that ensures software
freedom for all users, especially those who access the
software remotely. It requires that source code be made
available to all users, and any modifications must be
distributed under the same license. This license creates
an environment where software can be studied, modified, and
shared by anyone, preventing the software from being
converted into proprietary code.
